Long-term outcome of oligodendrogliomas.

Lebrun C(1), Fontaine D, Ramaioli A, Vandenbos F, Chanalet S, Lonjon M, Michiels 
JF, Bourg V, Paquis P, Chatel M, Frenay M; Nice Brain Tumor Study Group.

Author information:
(1)Department of Neurology, Hôpital Pasteur, Nice, France. 
christine.lebrun-frenay@wanadoo.fr

BACKGROUND: Favorable prognostic factors for oligodendroglial tumors include age 
younger than 40 years, low tumor grade, and extent of resection.
