oligodendrogliomas diagnosed between 1995 and 2002.
METHODS: The tumors were rated histologically by the WHO classification as low 
grade (grade II) or anaplastic (grade III). One hundred patients were 
categorized into three groups: group A: grade II, group B: secondary grade III 
(low grade with anaplastic transformation during the follow-up), group C: de 
novo grade III. All patients were symptomatic at presentation and underwent 
